***************** Practice Quiz (Self-review: Create a navigation in Compose)****************

Question 1) In this exercise, which property of the NavHost is used to set the initial destination?    
modifier
startDestination
navController
 
Question 2) In this exercise, the composable function is used to add the routes for the for the NavHost.    
True
False

Question 3) In this exercise, which one of the following variables are created in the Destinations interface for defining the NavGraph.    
route
nodes
icon

*****************Answer******************

Question 1) startDestination
Question 2) True
Question 3) route






***************** Practice Quiz (Knowledge check: JetPack Navigation)****************


Question 1) Which among the following actions can start navigation? Select all that apply.
Clicking a tab item
Selecting an item from the list
Clicking a button
    
Question 2) Bottom Navigation only navigates to a new destination without showing the status of the active item.
True
False

Question 3) Select all that apply. The fixed start navigation principle states that:     
The application always starts from the same screen but ends with a different screen.   
The application always ends with the same starting screen while leaving the app.
The application always starts from the same first screen. 

Question 4
The Stack works on which one of the following principles?
Last in Last out
Last in First out
First in First out
First in Last out

Question 5) Select all that apply. 

The purpose of NavHost is to:               
manage the Back Stack.
take the NavController as a parameter and associate it with the NavGraph.
act as a container for displaying the current destination.




*****************Answer******************

Question 1) Clicking a tab item
            Selecting an item from the list
            Clicking a button
Question 2) False
Question 3) The application always ends with the same starting screen while leaving the app.
            The application always starts from the same first screen. 
Question 4) Last in First out
Question 5) take the NavController as a parameter and associate it with the NavGraph.
            act as a container for displaying the current destination.





***************** Practice Quiz (Self-review: Create a scrollable gallery)****************


Question 1) In this exercise, which function did you call to make the Column Scrollable?    
 Modifier.verticallScroll()    
 Modifier.horizontalScroll()    
 Modifier.imeNestedScroll()    

Question 2) In this exercise, which property is used for arranging Row items?    
 horizontalArrangement
 verticalArrangement

Question 3) In this exercise, which one of the following approaches was used to populate the Grid?    
 forEach method
 repeat method
 forEachIndexed method



*****************Answer******************

Question 1) Modifier.verticallScroll() 
Question 2) horizontalArrangement
Question 3) repeat method




***************** Practice Quiz (Knowledge check: Lists and Grids)****************

Question 1) Which among the following can be used to place its children horizontally?
Row
Column

Question 2) Which one of the following arrangements adds space to the first and last child on the list while keeping other items in the center?    
Space Evenly
Space between
Space around

Question 3) Which of the following arrangements can be used with a Column?    
Both Vertical and Horizontal Arrangements
Horizontal Arrangement
Vertical Arrangement

Question 4) Scrolling is available to a Row and a Column without adding any modifier.    
True
False

Question 5) For creating a Grid of a small number of elements, a combination of Row and Column composable can be used.    
True
False


*****************Answer******************

Question 1) Row
Question 2) Space around
Question 3) Vertical Arrangement
Question 4) False
Question 5) True





